Metro claimed on its front page that non-Covid deaths are 'soaring'. This refers just to deaths in private homes, not all deaths.

There is evidence that the numbers of deaths from some diseases across all locations are in line with historical averages.

text.1:
Andrew Marr challenged Michael Gove saying that trading with the EU on “Australian terms” could well be called “Afghan” terms. 

Afghanistan actually has more favourable trade terms with the EU, at least as far as tariffs are concerned, than Australia.

text.2:
Covid cases are recorded by the address stored by your GP.

So it's true that students who haven’t registered with a new GP at university will be listed at their home address.

There's no way of knowing exactly how many students this is likely to affect.
